Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.00,0:13:39.25,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,Somewhere between fifty to a hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.25,0:13:41.25,Main,Paula,0,0,0,,Sorry. Not happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.57,0:13:48.61,Main,Paula,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, why would you suddenly \Nstart such nuts and bolts training?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.61,0:13:52.76,Main,Paula,0,0,0,,Did seeing a demon in person suddenly\Nmake you realize your responsibility?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.64,0:14:00.77,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,Is that what it looks like, Paula?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.47,0:14:06.03,Italics,Paula,0,0,0,,That's the face he makes when he's \Ngot something really nasty in mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.15,0:14:10.53,Main,Hayato,0,0,0,,Hey, Granny, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.53,0:14:11.41,Main,Rin,0,0,0,,What's what?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.41,0:14:13.43,Main,Hayato,0,0,0,,You've got something on your clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.43,0:14:15.72,Main,Hayato,0,0,0,,Some tiny metal thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.94,0:14:18.16,Main,Rin,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.48,0:14:20.38,Main,Hayato,0,0,0,,Some kinda machine, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.83,0:14:23.39,Main,Hayato,0,0,0,,What's it doing on you, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.39,0:14:24.42,Main,Rin,0,0,0,,I have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.42,0:14:29.34,Main,Hayato,0,0,0,,C'mon, what'd you have to break it for? \NYsley might've been able to figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.34,0:14:33.39,Main,Rin,0,0,0,,Doesn't matter. Once it's broken, \Nit's not anything anymore, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.03,0:14:35.83,Main,Hayato,0,0,0,,Yeah, guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.57,0:14:38.27,Italics,Narrator,0,0,0,,Oh, but it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.23,0:14:46.99,Main,Headline sign,0,0,0,,{\an2\fnArial\fs12\shad0\frz13\fax.1\c&H2C373E&\3c&HF9F6FB&\b1\pos(315.143,156.286)}Gend Autonomous Zone Invaded and Occupied by Zoble Forces
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.99,0:14:52.36,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,Paula, remember how I told you we're born \Nfrom the thoughts of living creatures?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.87,0:14:56.92,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,The thing is, thoughts alone \Ndon't make us manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.92,0:14:59.00,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,It takes an additional element...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.00,0:15:01.13,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,A desire for salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.55,0:15:07.98,Main,Mom,0,0,0,,It's okay. Don't be scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.26,0:15:10.54,Main,Grandma,0,0,0,,Dear God...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.60,0:15:16.19,Main,Father,0,0,0,,Please, God...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.98,0:15:25.39,Main,Gill,0,0,0,,Please... grant us salvation...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.39,0:15:26.48,Main,Gill,0,0,0,,God!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.49,0:15:32.49,Main,Paula,0,0,0,,That doesn't make any sense, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.84,0:15:36.69,Main,Paula,0,0,0,,You said human desire for salvation \Nis what makes Idaten appear,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.69,0:15:39.96,Main,Paula,0,0,0,,but we don't help humans at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.96,0:15:45.09,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,That's not so strange. It's other humans \Nwho make humans suffer in war, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.51,0:15:49.21,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,What sense would it make \Nto fight humans to save humans?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.09,0:15:51.59,Main,Paula,0,0,0,,I guess you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.59,0:15:55.25,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,Two human nations fight, \Nand one is destroyed...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.25,0:15:59.22,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,The victor grows in its place, \Nso it's not a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.22,0:16:02.80,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,It's not as if the humans care about how \Nthe composition of a forest might change
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.80,0:16:04.73,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,as long as there are still plants there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.73,0:16:08.03,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,And if an invasive species wipes \Nout the native wildlife of a lake,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.03,0:16:10.24,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,they'd just think of it \Nas a good fishing spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.24,0:16:13.06,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,This is all to say that, \Nwhile we're in a different position,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.48,0:16:16.50,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,our thought process isn't \Nso different from the humans'.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.01,0:16:21.50,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,Still, there's a condition under which\Nwe will fight to protect them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.50,0:16:23.40,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,Consider the demons...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.40,0:16:29.07,Main,,0,0,0,,For example, say you happened upon that Gyudo\Nmonster attacking some humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.07,0:16:32.02,Main,,0,0,0,,If you were as powerful as Rin-san,\N what would you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.81,0:16:34.01,Main,Paula,0,0,0,,I think I'd get rid of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.75,0:16:38.84,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,Yet why would you help humans \Nthat you normally just ignore?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.47,0:16:41.99,Main,Paula,0,0,0,,Huh, that's a good question...\N I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.99,0:16:45.38,Main,Paula,0,0,0,,I guess because I'd feel\N compelled to fight the monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.38,0:16:48.84,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,Wrong. It's because if you do nothing,\Nthe humans would be wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.29,0:16:53.02,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,Humans are similar. If a forest they \Nnormally don't care about catches on fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.50,0:16:55.03,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,they'll make an effort to put it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.03,0:16:58.66,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,But right now, mankind is distinctly \N{\i1}not{\i0} on the brink of destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.05,0:17:00.49,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,They're prosperous enough
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.49,0:17:03.95,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,to kill one another for simple \Nself-interest, of all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.67,0:17:08.63,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,And as humans engage in pointless \Nwars to amuse themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.96,0:17:11.05,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,the collective thoughts of those\N caught in the crossfire
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.38,0:17:14.55,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,is what calls us forth... to do nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.55,0:17:16.55,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,Thus we do nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.55,0:17:20.72,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,I suppose you could say we're a generation \Nof Idaten deities who only know peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.36,0:17:30.71,Italics,Gill,0,0,0,,Is there no God after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.36,0:17:36.32,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,Still, there's something I don't understand.\N What purpose do the demons serve?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.69,0:17:37.83,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,Did you know, Paula?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.57,0:17:42.33,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,If left uncontested, \Nthey'd continue to predate and destroy
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.33,0:17:45.85,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,until the world was completely barren
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.85,0:17:48.33,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,and they ultimately died from starvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.83,0:17:51.95,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,It doesn't make any sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.95,0:17:55.34,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,If there are any intelligent \Ndemons out there...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.49,0:18:00.89,Main,Ys,0,0,0,,I would love to ask what they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.76,0:18:04.77,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,Hey! Pi-chan, Pi-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.77,0:18:08.27,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,Long time no see! \NYou been doin' good, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.27,0:18:11.15,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,It's been a few years since \NI last saw you, right? Right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.15,0:18:14.00,Italics,Piscala,0,0,0,,The way she talks is still annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.00,0:18:15.11,Main,Piscala,0,0,0,,Nickel!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.11,0:18:18.15,Main,Piscala,0,0,0,,You need to show more respect \Nto a superior officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.83,0:18:23.66,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, you're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.66,0:18:27.79,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,I need'st be formal with my manner \Nof speech, do I not, General Piscalat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.02,0:18:31.79,Main,Troop,0,0,0,,How'd she survive a fall from that height?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.79,0:18:36.29,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,Putting that aside, this meeting \Nshould be of incredible import!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.29,0:18:40.30,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,I dare say we're in for the first \Nmeeting of substance in quite some time!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.91,0:18:45.23,Main,Biarov,0,0,0,,Your Majesty,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.23,0:18:48.73,Caption base,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fs16\pos(160.571,61.143)\fad(1270,1)}Prime Minister of the Zoble Empire\N{\fs30}Biarov
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.23,0:18:48.73,Main,Biarov,0,0,0,,why am I not a part of this meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.73,0:18:51.37,Main,Takeshita,0,0,0,,Because it has nothing to do with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.91,0:18:55.46,Caption base,Sign,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs12\pos(556,198.286)\fad(1005,1000)}Emperor of the Zoble Empire\N{\fs24}Takeshita
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.91,0:18:55.46,Caption base,Sign,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs12\fad(1005,1000)\pos(57.143,234.286)}Empress\N{\fs24}Brandy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.37,0:18:54.29,Main,Brandy,0,0,0,,That's right. Your job is running \Nthe government, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.29,0:18:57.24,Main,Brandy,0,0,0,,Just focus on policy and diplomacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.24,0:19:00.81,Italics,Biarov,0,0,0,,What the hell kind of diplomacy could a \Nwar-mongering nation like this manage?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.81,0:19:03.37,Main,Biarov,0,0,0,,As you wish, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.19,0:19:07.38,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,Hey there, Your Majesty the Emperor!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.85,0:19:11.78,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,You're looking as miserable as ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.78,0:19:15.10,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,We'll be waiting in the\N meeting room! Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.10,0:19:19.71,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,I must say, formal language is most tiring,\N don't you think, General Piscalat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.71,0:19:21.34,Main,Piscala,0,0,0,,You're not even pulling it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.99,0:19:24.54,Main,Brandy,0,0,0,,Nickel certainly seems to be in high spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.54,0:19:26.07,Main,Brandy,0,0,0,,We should get going ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.07,0:19:27.70,Main,Takeshita,0,0,0,,Yes, I suppose we should.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.63,0:19:33.85,Italics,Biarov,0,0,0,,This meeting was called by Obami,\N head of weapons development...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.85,0:19:36.93,Italics,Biarov,0,0,0,,What is that madman's game now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.93,0:19:37.94,Main,Biarov,0,0,0,,Kagekiki.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.94,0:19:38.57,Main,Kage,0,0,0,,Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.57,0:19:41.19,Main,Biarov,0,0,0,,I want you to look into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.19,0:19:43.07,Main,Kage,0,0,0,,By your command.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.07,0:19:45.07,Main,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fnArial\b1\shad0\bord0\pos(323.429,112.857)\c&H08090C&}Meeting Room
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.07,0:19:47.29,Caption base,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fs12\fad(1005,1)\pos(273.143,314.857)}Commander of the Zoble Imperial Navy\N{\fs18}Neput
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.07,0:19:47.29,Caption base,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fs12\fad(1005,1)\pos(100.571,157.143)}Child Soldier\N{\fs18}Cory
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.29,0:19:50.00,Caption base,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fs12\fad(1005,1)\pos(409.143,46.857)}Zoble Army Defense Force Soldier\N{\fs18}G-Thirteen
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.29,0:19:50.00,Caption base,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fs12\fad(1005,1)\pos(553.715,199.429)}The Lively Chief Clerk\Nof Childcare Support\N{\fs18}Barcode
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.29,0:19:50.00,Caption base,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fs12\fad(1005,1)\pos(142.286,230.857)}Star Midwife\N{\fs18}Umeyo
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.00,0:19:52.25,Caption base,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(111.429,77.714)\fs16\fad(1005,1)}Animal Trainer\N{\fs24}Miku
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.25,0:19:53.50,Caption base,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(323.429,212.571)}And everybody else
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.05,0:19:55.55,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,Is that everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.55,0:19:57.50,Main,Takeshita,0,0,0,,The doctor's not here yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.11,0:20:01.63,Caption base,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fs12\fad(1005,1)\pos(81.714,76.571)}PM Biarov's Personal Agent\N{\fs18}Kagekiki the Ninja
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.33,0:20:01.63,Italics,Kage,0,0,0,,What a bizarre assemblage...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.63,0:20:03.95,Italics,Kage,0,0,0,,What do they mean to discuss?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.93,0:20:08.93,Main,Obami,0,0,0,,Sorry about the delay, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.93,0:20:11.94,Caption base,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fad(1005,1)\fs16\pos(465.143,198.857)}Head of Weapons Development\N{\fs24}Doctor Obami
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.38,0:20:11.94,Main,Obami,0,0,0,,Let's get this meeting underway.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.42,0:20:19.25,Main,Piscalat,0,0,0,,What happened to you...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.25,0:20:24.16,Main,Obami,0,0,0,,Shut it! My usual body got \Nwrecked by that Idaten brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.16,0:20:27.06,Italics,Kage,0,0,0,,His "usual body"? It was wrecked?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.06,0:20:29.54,Italics,Kage,0,0,0,,And what exactly is an Idaten?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.54,0:20:33.84,Main,Obami,0,0,0,,Granted, that's part of why \Nwe're having this meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.84,0:20:35.81,Main,Obami,0,0,0,,First, let's start with...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.81,0:20:38.11,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,Oh, can I take care of one thing first?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.11,0:20:39.42,Main,Obami,0,0,0,,What is it, Nickel?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.47,0:20:50.72,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,Would you look at that!\NIf isn't Kagekiki-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.72,0:20:53.73,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,Look, I understand being curious...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.73,0:20:56.73,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,But eavesdropping is just rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.94,0:21:01.78,Main,Nickel,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry about that, Take-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.78,0:21:03.70,Main,Takeshita,0,0,0,,Try to be more careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.18,0:21:07.53,Main,Brandy,0,0,0,,Now, we're ready when you are...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.53,0:21:13.54,Main,Brandy,0,0,0,,O great Demon Lord who granted \Nus human forms and intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.54,0:21:17.48,Main,Obami,0,0,0,,All right, let's start by reviewing \Nthe footage of the Idaten.
